****************************************
a.user
****************************************
1.Check the current user
  command : whoami
> it shows the current username 

2.Check the user details
  command : id username
>it shows the userid(uuid),groupid(ggid) and groups ,details about the user

3.Create a new usrname 
  command : useradd username

  example : useradd jagan

>user name are placed in the :cd /home

4.Set the password to the username
  command : passwd username

  example : passwd jagan 

5.To switch the one user account to another user
  command : su -
    su=switch user

  command : su - jagan

6.View the password files in system
  command : cat /etc/shadow

7.Check the user list
  command :cat /etc/passwd

8.To delete the username with home directory
  command :userdel -r username

9.To delete the user acoount from the system 
  command : userdel username
********************************************
b.group commands
********************************************
1.Create a new group 
  command : groupadd groupname

2.Modify the group name
  command : groupmod -n new name old name

3.Delete the group name
  command : groupdel groupname

********************************************
c.usermod
********************************************
1.Add user to the group
  command : usermod -aG groupname username

 >Check the user can add the group
   cat /etc/group

2.change the username 
  command : usermod -l newname oldname

3.Lock the user account 
  command : usermod -L username

  example:usermod -L manage jagan

4.Check the user acount is locked or not
  command : passwd -S username

  example : passwd -S jagan

5.Unlock the user account
  command : usermod -U username

  example : usermod -U jagan

   >Apply the command to check user user accout is unlock
  command : passwd -S jagan
*******************************************************
d.chage
*******************************************************
1.List of password agging information
  command : chage -l username

  example : chage -l jagan

2.Set maximum password 
  command : chage -M days username

  example : chage -M 11 jagan

3.Set minimum password age
  command : chage -m days jagan

4.Set warning before password expiry
  command : chage -W days username

5.Set Account expiry date
  command : chage -E yyyy-mm-dd username

6.Set password to never expire
  command : chage -m -1 username

7.Set account to never expire
  command : chage -E -1 username 

8.Set password inactive days
  command : chage -I days username

9.Disable the inactive lock
  command : chage -I -1 username
