User permissions 
***********************************************
there are three types of permissions 
1. read(r)
2. write(w)
3. execute(x)

number                permissions
----------            ------------
0                       ---
1                       --x
2                       -w-    
3                       -wx  
4                       r--
5                       r-x
6                       rw-
7                       rwx


1.Change the owner only

 command : chown username directory name

 example : chown jagan continered

2.Change owner and group 
 command : chown user:group directory name

 example : chown jagan:bottle continered

3.Change the ownership for all files inside the directory name
 command : chown -R username:groupname directory name

 example : chown -R jagan:bottle continered

5.Change only group name 
 command : chown :groupname directory name

chmod : this command is used to give the permission to the files

 examples:  
    a.command : chmod 345 file name
    b.command : chmod 456 file name
    c.command : chmod 777 file name

>it gives directly permission to the file by using chmod command 


